# Python Environment Rules

## Python Environment
- **ALWAYS use pipenv** when running Python commands in this workspace
- Use `pipenv run python` instead of just `python`
- Use `pipenv run pip` instead of just `pip`
- Use `pipenv run pytest` instead of just `pytest`
- Use `pipenv shell` to activate the virtual environment if needed

## Examples
```bash
# ✅ Correct
pipenv run python -c "import dlt; print(dlt.__version__)"
pipenv run pytest tests/
pipenv run pip install new-package

# ❌ Incorrect
python -c "import dlt"
pytest tests/
pip install new-package
```

## Why This Matters
- This workspace uses pipenv for dependency management
- The virtual environment contains all required packages (dlt, pytest, etc.)
- Running Python commands without pipenv will result in ModuleNotFoundError
- This ensures consistency with the project's dependency management approach

## When to Use pipenv
- Running any Python script
- Installing packages
- Running tests
- Running Python REPL commands
- Any Python-related terminal operations
